name: Caoimhe LastName
description:
Happy St Patrick's Day! Caoimhe is the third in a new set of custom LastName characters, for anyone who wants a consistent character for their SD 1.5 renders.

Caoimhe is Irish. Her name is pronounced "Quee-vah". (For reals.) She might be a princess, an elf, a fairy, a warrior, or a mermaid. She might be a stereotype. Either way, she's definitely beautiful. If she smiles at you, it's over.

Note: The redness of Caoimhe's hair depends on the time of day. If in doubt, add long red hair to your prompt to be sure.

To use this embedding with the Automatic1111 web UI, save the downloaded file to /embeddings/caoimhelastnamesd15.pt, and then include the trigger word caoimhelastnamesd15 in your prompt.

(Inspired by Zovya's Nobody series, which is awesome. Go download all of their amazing characters.)

(All of the sample images have full metadata, and were generated with XpucT's Deliberate v2.)
